# ðŸ§˜ Example: The "ZenTasks" App (Full-Stack)

This example demonstrates how **Fader V2.0** handles both interface design and backend logic in a single file. 

By using the `DATA_MIX` block, we instruct the AI to build a **fully synced, authenticated cloud application** without writing any SQL or backend boilerplate.

### `zen_tasks.fdr`

```yaml
# FILE: zen_tasks.fdr

METADATA:
  App: "ZenTasks"
  Target: Lovable / Replit

PROMPT: 
  "A calming to-do list app. Users can type a task, hit enter to add it to a list, 
   and click a circle to check it off. Checked items should move to the bottom 
   and gently fade out."

UI_MIX:
  - Density: 20%      # Airy. Lots of breathing room, large text, easy on the eyes.
  - Pop: 10%          # Muted. Very subtle; maybe just a soft color change when checked.
  - Warmth: 100%      # Cozy. Beige background, soft rounded edges, serif fonts.
  - Strictness: 30%   # Organic. Slightly loose layout, not a rigid corporate table.
  - Motion: 90%       # Fluid. Tasks slide in smoothly and fade out gently.

DATA_MIX:
  - Persistence: 100% # Cloud. Save to Supabase (so I can see tasks on phone & laptop).
  - Reactivity: 100%  # Live. Real-time sync (WebSockets) across devices.
  - Privacy: 100%     # Private. Force a Login screen; users only see their own data.
  - Complexity: 10%   # Flat. Simple list structure; no complex folders or tags.

TECH:
  - Framework: React
  - Style: Tailwind
  - Backend: Supabase
